   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="edition" ana="#b1" xml:lang="grc" subtype="transcription" xml:id="elus0054.transcription" corresp="#elus0054.translation">
            <p>Θάρσ<lb break="no"/>ι Ἄαμερ<lb break="no"/>ος Οὐά<lb break="no"/>ελος ο<lb break="no"/>ὐδὶς άθ<lb break="no"/>
               <unclear>άν</unclear>
               <supplied reason="lost">ατος</supplied>
            </p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation" ana="#b1" xml:id="elus0054.translation" corresp="#elus0054.transcription">
            <p>Courage, 'Amir, son of Wa'il, no one is immortal</p>
         </div>
      </body>
      <back>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>The word Ἄαμερος could be the title "Emir" instead of the name 'Amir.' The editor
               thinks that the use of common formula "Courage" and "no one is immortal" mark
               tombstones in this group as pre-Christian.</p>
         </div>
